The seer will need at least 2 nights to determine for sure if they are insane or not (they would need 2 checks the same. Might take 3 nights if they hit a wolf and a villager) And even then, the incriminate pot and the assassin would also check as wolfpack, so it's not a sure thing.
3-4 nights is ideal for the seer to get reliable intel, but that's unlikely. Moreso if we FC early.

@ImmortlHog The issue with FC is exactly as you said, but image if we do a FC and both the wolf and the assassin claim holdout? Now we have 5 holdouts and a seer. We cant shoot or agitate until someone dies, and that will likely be the seer since they are the most likely to mess things up for the wolfpack team. Now we're just left with a bunch of holdout claims. Berserker is also tough, so even if we all shoot the person below us at that point, we only manage to kill the N1 target and the assassin, which gives the wolf 2 kills the following night and we would have no toughness left.
